                <head>165. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 4, a White House statement was issued by President
                        <persName>Eisenhower</persName> at the United States Naval Base, Newport,
                    Rhode Island, praising the delegates to the Buenos Aires Economic Conference for
                    “reaching a large measure of agreement on the important economic problems
                    confronting the American States.” The full text of the statement is printed in
                    Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, September 30, 1957, page
                    359.</p>
            </div>
